      "Resistance is the total opposition caused by the material, its length, and its thickness.",
      "Voltage drop is the loss of electrical pressure as current works against that resistance."
    ],
    "questionText": "An electrician replaces a standard copper cable with a different metal alloy cable that has a much higher resistivity. Explain how this change in the material's inherent property leads to an increased voltage drop at the end of the circuit run.",
    "answerGuidance": [
      "Higher resistivity increases the total resistance of the conductor.",
      "Current flowing through this higher resistance results in a greater loss of electrical pressure.",
      "This loss of electrical pressure is the definition of voltage drop."
    ],
    "hint": "Think about the chain of causality: how does the material's 'DNA' change the total opposition, and what does that do to the voltage?"
  }
}

